  "excerpt": "Francis Wolff's photographs preserve precious moments of some of the greatest musicians at work on some of the most enduring jazz recordings. The photographer of jazz whose work is art in itself is Roy DeCarava, but there's another crucial aspect of jazz history—the private side, of music made in recording studios—which is documented in Wolff's remarkable archive.",
